CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 26, 1953, pg. 1, reads: "SCHENLEY 'INSPIRATIONS' - Schenley High gridders will have oodles of beauty to inspire them in their gridiron battles this season. In addition to these beauties who act as cheerleaders at the games, the school has a majorette corps.  Putting their all into a call to 'fight for dear old Schenley' are...Top row, left to right, are: Maxine Cooper, Eunice Frishman, Clara Gillis and Fay Eisen. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of six Schenley High School cheerleaders, including Maxine Cooper, Eunice Frishman, Clara Gillis, Barbara Flood, Fay Eisen, and unknown, squatting on steps of Schenley High School
